Date: Tue 29 Mar 2011
From: Kim Klotins <kim.klotins@inspection.gc.ca> [edited]


[Re: ProMED-mail Epizootic ulcerative synd., fish - Canada
20110326.0952]
----------------------------------------------------------------------
I would like to ask a retraction to the Moderator's comment, that
follows, under this posting unless the Moderator otherwise has
evidence (none provided in the commentary):

"This is not the 1st report of this disease in Canada, but it is an
expansion of the disease."

To our knowledge, this disease has never been reported in Canada.
This is a geographic extension of distribution of the disease and an
extension of the range of susceptible species.

--
Kim Klotins, DVM, DVSc
Acting National Manager / Gestionnaire national interimaire
Disease Control & Contingency Planning / Lutte contre les maladies et
